Date: Sun, 29 Mar 2026 04:55:38 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] feat: rewrite OpenClawBridge to use WebSocket instead of REST

Replaces the HTTP POST /v1/chat/completions approach with the native
OpenClaw WebSocket protocol (chat.send + session.message events).

Changes:

OpenClawBridge now connects via WS, authenticates, subscribes to
session messages, and sends chat via chat.send method
Health check uses GET /health (always works, no config needed)
Absorbs OpenClawEventClient notification handling (heartbeat/cron)
GeminiSessionViewModel uses bridge.onNotification instead of
separate eventClient
invokeTool (POST /tools/invoke) unchanged - still HTTP
No gateway config changes required (chatCompletions endpoint
not needed)
This eliminates the dependency on gateway.http.endpoints.chatCompletions
which is disabled by default.
